BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Authority: Public Law 107-51\nReason: Public Law 107-51 provides for the U.S. flag to be lowered to half-staff from sunrise to sunset for the National Fallen Firefighters Memorial Service. This observance honors firefighters who died in service to their communities and invites the country to pause in gratitude for their sacrifice.\nSource: https://www.congress.gov/107/plaws/publ51/PLAW-107publ51.pdf
DTEND:20260504T000315Z
DTSTART:20260503T100915Z
SUMMARY:National Fallen Firefighters Memorial Service
UID:0dd7ee810aad3f49266affb8cf956b67cc42e578ad05ef051c4afb7bab9ae5fd
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Authority: 4 U.S.C. 6(d) and 4 U.S.C. 7(m)\nReason: The U.S. Flag Code provides that the flag is displayed at half-staff until noon on Memorial Day\, then raised to full-staff for the remainder of the day. The morning lowering honors those who died while serving in the U.S. Armed Forces\, while the noon raising symbolizes the nation carrying their legacy forward.\nSource: https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title4-section6&num=0&edition=prelim
DTEND:20260525T160000Z
DTSTART:20260525T094939Z
SUMMARY:Memorial Day
UID:bba0285fc5abb8dd67b425fb14a14831ea60e0e9ae656737926d8e88f2cacf5b
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Authority: Missouri Governor\nReason: In honor of Butler County Fire Protection District Shift Commander Jackson Warren\, Governor Mike Kehoe ordered flags to be flown at half-staff on March 12\, 2026\, from sunrise to sunset.\nSource: https://governor.mo.gov/press-releases/archive/governor-kehoe-orders-flags-fly-half-staff-honor-butler-county-fire
DTEND:20260313T001338Z
DTSTART:20260312T122602Z
SUMMARY:Governor Kehoe orders flags to half-staff in honor of Shift Commander Jackson Warren
