DESCRIPTION:Authority: 4 U.S.C. 7(m) and 36 U.S.C. 136\nReason: Federal law provides for the U.S. flag to be displayed at half-staff from sunrise to sunset on Peace Officers Memorial Day\, unless it falls on Armed Forces Day. The observance honors law enforcement officers who lost their lives in the line of duty and recognizes the service and sacrifice of peace officers across the country.\nSource: https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title36-section136&num=0&edition=prelim
DTEND:20260516T001442Z
DTSTART:20260515T095704Z
SUMMARY:Peace Officers Memorial Day
UID:ea45171955fd790049ed6ba313edec43154aae3452421cdb0a824a3e25d7a594
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Authority: 36 U.S.C. 144\nReason: Federal law requests that the U.S. flag be displayed at half-staff from sunrise to sunset on Patriot Day. The observance honors those killed in the September 11 attacks\, recognizes the bravery of responders\, and marks a national day of remembrance and resolve.\nSource: https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title36-section144&num=0&edition=prelim
DTEND:20260911T232516Z
DTSTART:20260911T104716Z
SUMMARY:Patriot Day
